data.enText: showing a tendency to commit crimes

before.enText: especially of young people or their behaviour

data.enText: having failed to pay money that is owed
data.chText: 拖欠债务的；欠债未还的

data.enText: not having been paid in time

tr: not paid at the scheduled time

example: remiss of you not to pay your bills

value.def: Someone, usually a young person, who is delinquent repeatedly commits minor crimes.
value.tran: (通常指青少年)常有违法行为的，屡犯轻罪的

value.def: A delinquent borrower or taxpayer is someone who has failed to pay their debts or taxes.
value.tran: 拖欠债务的;未缴税款的
